{
  "stem": "15396.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, then by chance, through Mrs.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Pell, I met Mr.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Mitchell.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know how I met him, actually, but I got to know him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was head of the intelligence service.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And Commander [INAUDIBLE], Richard [INAUDIBLE], you know, who sank boats in the [INAUDIBLE] Canal before, quite well-known.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was married to Betty Chester, one of the Co-Optimists.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I got to know these people-- Donald Darling in the British intelligence-- and I was hanging out with them a little bit.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then finally, we get these boats and go to-- to England, and with Bill Holland and this man, Eddie [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was-- you know, I was relieved, but I was sort of-- there was a point there where I felt why didn't I stay and do something else?",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Find another way, you know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I couldn't have, of course, because I was too much on the list.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you know, they'd photographed me and everything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I was thinking, why couldn't I find something else to do?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But then I was so anxious now for the RAF thinking, well, that's the best thing I can do.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I certainly can't do it anymore here.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, not really.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As I say, I was probably already quite ill, but my physical was quite all right.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had flown before, so that was-- that part was all right.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But then I went to a private doctor, and I had blood in my oxygen mask one time, and I--",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I went to a private doctor, and he reported me because I had on an RAF uniform, of course, and I had here, instead of USA, I had Virginia.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
